// SPDX-License-Identifier: PolyForm-Noncommercial-1.0.0
// oss-spec:allow-large-file: machine-generated data — one base64 portrait per
// demo contact; splitting would only scatter the dataset.
//
// Portrait photos for the demo address book, keyed by demo-contact slug
// (`buildDemoData` attaches each as the card's photo gallery). The faces are
// AI-generated portrait grids produced and owned by the repository owner,
// sliced into 128 px square JPEG crops (quality 62) — no real people, no
// third-party licensing. Faces were cast onto cards by apparent age and look
// (the comment on each entry records the source grid tile and the casting),
// so a 1950s-born parent wears an older face and the friends wear thirty-ish
// ones. Not every card has a photo — like a real address book.
//
// Regenerating: detect the grid's white gutter lines globally (runs of
// near-white rows/columns spanning the whole image) and cut tiles strictly
// between them — fixed insets miss, because the spacing drifts a few px
// between grids. Then square-crop, resize to 128 px, JPEG-encode, and map
// slugs to data URIs here. Verify by eye on a dark contact sheet before
// shipping. The one-off scripts live in the PRs that produced this file.

